            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod%20knew%20that%20people%20would%20battle%20two%20major%20enemies%3A%20pride%20and%20selfishness.%20He%20dealt%20with%20humanity's%20pride%20at%20Babel%20(Genesis%2011%3A1-9)%2C%20and%20in%20Genesis%2014%20He%20dealt%20with%20humanity's%20selfishness.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EAbraham%20was%20the%20first%20man%20recorded%20in%20the%20Scriptures%20to%20tithe%2C%20although%20Abel%20did%20offer%20the%20Lord%20%22choice%20lambs%20from%20the%20best%20of%20his%20flock%22%20(Genesis%204%3A4).%20Abraham's%20worship%20of%20God%20with%20ten%20percent%20of%20his%20revenue%20showed%20that%20he%20acknowledged%20his%20financial%20responsibility%20before%20God%20and%20knew%20that%20God%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20would%20take%20care%20of%20his%20needs.%20By%20refusing%20the%20king%20of%20Sodom's%20reward%20(Genesis%2014%3A21-23)%2C%20Abraham%20rejected%20the%20world's%20system.%20God%20became%20his%20reward%20(his%20salary%2C%20wages%2C%20and%20compensation)%2C%20and%20God%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20recompensed%20Abraham%20with%20something%20that%20money%20could%20not%20buy%3A%20a%20child!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3ETithing%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20Abraham's%20covenant%20with%20God.%20God%20reciprocated%20and%20pledged%20all%20His%20assets%20to%20Abraham%2C%20even%20unto%20the%20fourth%20generation%20(Genesis%2015%3A14-16).%20Abraham%20further%20exemplified%20an%20unselfish%20spirit%20when%20he%20gave%20Lot%20the%20first%20choice%20of%20where%20to%20live.%20The%20final%20result%20was%20that%20Abraham%20profited%20much%20more%20than%20Lot%20because%20he%20obeyed%20the%20principle%20of%20unselfish%20sacrifice%20for%20others%20(Genesis%2013).%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%3EWant%20to%20be%20blessed%3F%20Be%20a%20tither!%3C%2Fp%3E"
        },
